{
  "stem": "11174.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And my sister-- married sister-- I had a sister, Hinda, that was married.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "She was younger than my brother, but through some sort circumstances, she was married a little before him.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And she was married with a fellow from the same town where the zayde lived.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So she was still there, and I was there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My father said, that's too much going on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "You know, in the air there was such a nervousness, talking so and so thick about the war.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So he went back to our little town.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "He said, I still have young children.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And he went back, and this is the last time I saw him.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I was there with my grandfather and my sister-- my sister with her husband.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And after the war broke out, which was on a Friday, September the 1st, everybody got nervous, and everybody was thinking about running.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So my-- finally, the next Tuesday they were saying that the Germans are not far, and the army is coming in.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So we started up to walk.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We wanted to buy horse and buggies.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We couldn't buy anything anymore.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And we started walking, and everybody thought it's going to be what they used to call in-- in a German word in Yiddish, [YIDDISH], [? they called it ?] [YIDDISH].",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "It means moving [INAUDIBLE] trains.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] It was so different between-- so we walked and walked until about 30 people went with the zayde because he was that spiritual leader, the rebbe.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All right.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then we'll catch up to that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "All right.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now as I mentioned just now, my sister was the second.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Her name was Hinda.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And her husband's name was Moishe Kapler from that same town, Briegel.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the father was also a rabbi, a great scholar.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
